     6	//! `EmbedderChoice::Caller(Arc::new(OrtBgeEmbedder::…))` — the engine never
     7	//! names it, so there is ZERO engine change (ADR-0.8.16-onnx-embedder-backend
     8	//! §2). The `Default` variant stays candle-only, preserving the footprint
     9	//! invariant.
    10	//!
    11	//! Why ONNX at all: candle reaches only CPU / CUDA / Metal — no AMD ROCm,
    12	//! Intel OpenVINO, or Windows DirectML. ONNX Runtime reaches all of those, so
    13	//! this backend is the cross-vendor reach-hardware path (ADR §1). It is behind
    14	//! the NON-default `onnx-embedder` Cargo feature so the thin default build
    15	//! gains zero deps (EMB-3 wheel-size gate).
