The runtime code compiles in the checked feature combinations, but the export tooling can silently generate the ONNX asset from unpinned weights, undermining the correctness of the new backend and its equivalence data.

Review comment:

- [P2] Fail closed when the pinned HF snapshot is missing — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/0.8.16-slice-10-20260708T192441Z/dev/tools/onnx/export_bge_small_onnx.py:68-74
  When the exact pinned revision is absent but any other local BGE snapshot exists, this fallback exports that arbitrary snapshot while the ADR/README and `HF_REVISION`-based identity still describe the candle-pinned weights. `--verify` will still pass because it only checks byte determinism, so a host with a newer cached snapshot can silently produce a non-reference ONNX asset and invalidate the candle↔ONNX equivalence measurement; this should error instead of falling back.
